**To wire these up, you'll also need a `playwright.config.ts` and a `global-setup.ts` that calls `saveAdminAuthState`. Key points:**

- Run `npx playwright install chromium` once
- Add `globalSetup: './automation/ui/global-setup.ts'` to your config
- The `.auth/` directory is git-ignored (contains session tokens)
- Tests tagged with `storageState` will skip the login form entirely — only `global-setup` authenticates once per run
